#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3277
#, no-c-format
msgid "An LDIF File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# The Organization\n"
"dn: dc=example,dc=com\n"
"objectClass: dcObject\n"
"objectClass: organization\n"
"o: Example dc: example\n"
"\n"
"# The organizational unit development (devel)\n"
"dn: ou=devel,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"objectClass: organizationalUnit\n"
"ou: devel\n"
"\n"
"# The organizational unit documentation (doc)\n"
"dn: ou=doc,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"objectClass: organizationalUnit\n"
"ou: doc\n"
"\n"
"# The organizational unit internal IT (it)\n"
"dn: ou=it,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"objectClass: organizationalUnit\n"
"ou: it"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the file with the <filename>.ldif</filename> suffix then pass it to the "
"server with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ldapadd -x -D <replaceable>dn_of_the_administrator</replaceable> -W -f "
"<replaceable>file</replaceable>.ldif"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: primary
#: security_ldap.xml:3285 security_ldap.xml:3347 security_ldap.xml:3386
#: security_ldap.xml:3418
#, no-c-format
msgid "commands"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>-x</literal> switches off the authentication with SASL in this "
"case. <literal>-D</literal> declares the user that calls the operation. The "
"valid DN of the administrator is entered here, as it has been configured in "
"<filename>slapd.conf</filename>. In the current example, this is "
"<literal>cn=Administrator,dc=example,dc=com</literal>. <literal>-W</literal> "
"circumvents entering the password on the command line (in clear text) and "
"activates a separate password prompt. The <literal>-f</literal> option "
"passes the file name. See the details of running <command>ldapadd</command> "
"in <xref linkend=\"aus.ldap.addentry\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3303
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldapadd with example.ldif"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ldapadd -x -D cn=Administrator,dc=example,dc=com -W -f example.ldif\n"
"\n"
"Enter LDAP password:\n"
"adding new entry \"dc=example,dc=com\"\n"
"adding new entry \"ou=devel,dc=example,dc=com\"\n"
"adding new entry \"ou=doc,dc=example,dc=com\"\n"
"adding new entry \"ou=it,dc=example,dc=com\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The user data of individuals can be prepared in separate LDIF files. <xref "
"linkend=\"aus.ldap.addtux\"/> adds <systemitem class=\"username\">Tux</"
"systemitem> to the new LDAP directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3312
#, no-c-format
msgid "LDIF Data for Tux"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# coworker Tux\n"
"dn: cn=Tux Linux,ou=devel,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"objectClass: inetOrgPerson\n"
"cn: Tux Linux\n"
"givenName: Tux\n"
"sn: Linux\n"
"mail: tux@example.com\n"
"uid: tux\n"
"telephoneNumber: +49 1234 567-8"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3315
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An LDIF file can contain an arbitrary number of objects. It is possible to "
"pass directory branches (entirely or in part) to the server in one go, as "
"shown in the example of individual objects. If it is necessary to modify "
"some data relatively often, a fine subdivision of single objects is "
"recommended."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3325
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modifying Data in the LDAP Directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: security_ldap.xml:3327
#, no-c-format
msgid "modifying data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: security_ldap.xml:3329 security_ldap.xml:3348
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldapmodify"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3330
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The tool <command>ldapmodify</command> is provided for modifying the data "
"stock. The easiest way to do this is to modify the corresponding LDIF file "
"and pass the modified file to the LDAP server. To change the telephone "
"number of colleague Tux from <literal>+49 1234 567-8</literal> to <literal>"
"+49 1234 567-10</literal>, edit the LDIF file like in <xref linkend=\"aus."
"ldap.ldif.tux\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modified LDIF File tux.ldif"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# coworker Tux\n"
"dn: cn=Tux Linux,ou=devel,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"changetype: modify\n"
"replace: telephoneNumber\n"
"telephoneNumber: +49 1234 567-10"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Import the modified file into the LDAP directory with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3346
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldapmodify -x -D cn=Administrator,dc=example,dc=com -W -f tux.ldif"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, pass the attributes to change directly to "
"<command>ldapmodify</command> as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3355
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start <command>ldapmodify</command> and enter your password:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ldapmodify -x -D cn=Administrator,dc=example,dc=com -W\n"
"Enter LDAP password:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter the changes while carefully complying with the syntax in the order "
"presented below:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"dn: cn=Tux Linux,ou=devel,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"changetype: modify\n"
"replace: telephoneNumber\n"
"telephoneNumber: +49 1234 567-10"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information about <command>ldapmodify</command> and its syntax, see "
"the <command>ldapmodify</command> man page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3375
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searching or Reading Data from an LDAP Directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: security_ldap.xml:3377
#, no-c-format
msgid "searching data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: security_ldap.xml:3379 security_ldap.xml:3387
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldapsearch"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"OpenLDAP provides, with <command>ldapsearch</command>, a command line tool "
"for searching data within an LDAP directory and reading data from it. This "
"is a simple query:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3385
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldapsearch -x -b dc=example,dc=com \"(objectClass=*)\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>-b</option> option determines the search base (the section of "
"the tree within which the search should be performed). In the current case, "
"this is <literal>dc=example,dc=com</literal>. To perform a more finely-"
"grained search in specific subsections of the LDAP directory (for example, "
"only within the <literal>devel</literal> department), pass this section to "
"<command>ldapsearch</command> with <option>-b</option>. <option>-x</option> "
"requests activation of simple authentication. <literal>(objectClass=*)</"
"literal> declares that all objects contained in the directory should be "
"read. This command option can be used after the creation of a new directory "
"tree to verify that all entries have been recorded correctly and the server "
"responds as desired. For more information about the use of "
"<command>ldapsearch</command>, see the <systemitem>ldapsearch(1)</"
"systemitem> man page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:3406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deleting Data from an LDAP Directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: security_ldap.xml:3408
#, no-c-format
msgid "deleting data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: security_ldap.xml:3410 security_ldap.xml:3419
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldapdelete"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:3411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Delete unwanted entries with <command>ldapdelete</command>. The syntax is "
"similar to that of the other commands. To delete, for example, the complete "
"entry for <literal>Tux Linux</literal>, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_ldap.xml:3417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ldapdelete -x -D cn=Administrator,dc=example,dc=com -W cn=Tux \\\n"
"Linux,ou=devel,dc=example,dc=com"
msgstr ""

